The paper deals with polyhedra and their Hamiltonian paths, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of unfolding surfaces to a common net is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the study of infinite classes, which is a common theme in computer science theory (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.SI).
